  "body": "## üìã Overview\n\nThis PR implements the foundational ECS components for the Combat MVP system as specified in issue #128. It provides the basic building blocks needed for combat mechanics in the Goblin Camp colony management game.\n\n## üéØ Changes Made\n\n### ‚öîÔ∏è Core Combat Components\n- **Faction & FactionKind**: Defines entity allegiance (Goblins, Invaders, Neutral) with hostility rules\n- **Health**: Tracks HP with damage/healing methods, clamping, and life/death checks\n- **CombatStats**: Combat capabilities (accuracy, evasion, attack, defense, damage range)\n- **AttackCooldown**: Timing system to prevent rapid attacks\n- **Combatant**: Marker component for entities that can participate in combat\n- **Dead**: Marker component for deceased entities\n- **Target**: Lightweight targeting component for combat systems\n\n### üîß Technical Features\n- **Save/Load Support**: All components derive Serialize/Deserialize for persistence\n- **Deterministic Simulation**: Integer-only math for consistent results\n- **Comprehensive Validation**: Proper validation and clamping in constructors\n- **Helper Methods**: Common operations (damage, healing, hit chance calculations)\n- **Full Test Coverage**: Unit tests for all components and methods\n\n## üìã Issue Links\n- **Issue**: #128 (Combat MVP core components)\n\n## üè∑Ô∏è Labels\n- `enhancement` - New feature implementation\n- `area:combat` - Combat system development\n- `size:M` - Medium-sized feature (0.5-1d)\n\n## ‚úÖ Acceptance Criteria Met\n- ‚úÖ Components and enums added under gc_core with module docs\n- ‚úÖ serde derives compile (behind existing feature flags)\n- ‚úÖ Unit tests cover Health clamps, invariants, and constructors\n- ‚úÖ Round-trip serde for each component (except Target due to Entity limitations)\n- ‚úÖ No public API breaks in existing modules\n\n## üîß Quality Assurance\n- All copilot review feedback addressed:\n  - Added validation for negative max_hp in Health constructors\n  - Fixed Health::full() to use Self::new() for consistent validation\n  - Added Serialize/Deserialize derives to Combatant and Dead marker components\n  - Comprehensive validation prevents panics and invalid states\n\n## üéØ Impact\nThis provides the foundation for follow-up combat systems including targeting, movement, attack resolution, and death handling. The components are designed for deterministic simulation and full save/load compatibility.",
